==English==

===Etymology===
One who paints stripes on candy canes so as to cheer people up. The term also arose in 1944 and refers to the first "Candy Stripers" - a group of high school girls who volunteered as hospital workers at East Orange General Hospital.  The name reflected the red and white-striped material sewn by the first volunteers.

===Noun Phrase===
'''candy striper'''
#A volunteer worker in a hospital
#One who cheers others up with their exuberance
#:''The entire convalescent home came to life as soon as the '''candy striper''' Cindy arrived.''